257
00:15:20,410 --> 00:15:22,420
Now, look at it from
my point of view.

258
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,320
We can't say.

259
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:29,440
There's no way I can say
that that is a homicide.

260
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:33,520
There's no way of telling
how, why this man died.

261
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:38,520
Except, there is a way
to tell how that man died:

262
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:41,430
a medical investigation
into his death,

263
00:15:41,490 --> 00:15:44,300
which happens to be
your exact job.

264
00:15:44,420 --> 00:15:47,370
Like hearing a clown say:
"There is no way to twist"

265
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:49,450
"this balloon into
a shape of a dog or hat."

266
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:53,410
Really, clown? If that's true,
what exactly is the use of you,

267
00:15:53,430 --> 00:15:57,280
other than psychologically damaging
children for life?

268
00:15:57,450 --> 00:16:02,490
That case was later re-classified
as a homicide, because it was.

269
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,390
It is no wonder

270
00:16:04,410 --> 00:16:08,380
that medical organizations have
been calling for the coroner system

271
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,520
to be abolished since 1857,

272
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:15,280
arguing that the person appointed
should be a doctor in medicine,

273
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:17,420
essentially,
the medical examiner system.

274
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:22,500
Instinctively does sound better!
Even this system is not perfect.

275
00:16:23,180 --> 00:16:26,230
The place where staff
posed for photos with a severed head?

276
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:28,280
That was
a medical examiner's office.

277
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,250
The guy who took the brain
for his kids to play with?

278
00:16:31,270 --> 00:16:33,310
He was and still is
a medical examiner.

279
00:16:33,350 --> 00:16:36,320
And that's not even
mentioning the medical examiner

280
00:16:36,340 --> 00:16:40,260
at the center of the most fantastic
"20/20" interview of all time.

281
00:16:41,210 --> 00:16:45,350
The other charge is that your dog
ate one of the body's spleen

282
